        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 11:39AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 1139 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles northeast of Smith Point to Gilchrist.
Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gilchrist, Rollover Pass, High Island, Bolivar Peninsula, Stowell,
and Oak Island.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
